<L>__{exterior camp day}
<A>__{they have stopped to make camp. it is late afternoon, the sky just darkening, sharp shadows on the far peaks, a purple glow in the air.}
<C>__{bobby}
<D>__{we won't have a fire tonight. we should make a shelter though, in case it snows.}
<C>__{hector}
<D>__{what about bears, without a fire?}
<A>__{bobby laughs quietly.}
<C>__{bobby}
<D>__{don't even think about bears, hector.}
<L>__{exterior camp night}
<A>__{they are making a round frame of bent branches and cover ing it with foliage. half hidden in the undergrowth, it is big enough for two men to huddle in. tonight they feel the most basic of urges, to curl up in a ball and hide.}
